 - Rijndael is **not** AES, in the sense that it&#39;s not implementing the actual AES standard. If this is for production use, I&#39;d suggest moving to actual AES (take a look at [this link](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/archive/blogs/shawnfa/the-differences-between-rijndael-and-aes) for info).
